    "text_1": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Fashion and sport collide in the latest adidas collaboration, blending street style with high performance. The new <strong>adidas x JAY3LLE capsule</strong> has arrived to redefine women\u2019s golf fashion, making a bold statement both on and off the course. Designed by <strong>Johan Lindeberg</strong>, co-founder of the luxury fashion label JAY3LLE, in partnership with his daughter <strong>Blue Lindeberg</strong>, this collection aims to empower women golfers with powerful, fashion-forward silhouettes.</p><p></p><h1><strong>The Vision Behind adidas x JAY3LLE</strong></h1><h2><strong>A Creative Collaboration Rooted in Passion</strong></h2><p>Johan Lindeberg, a fashion visionary who revolutionised golf fashion in the late 1990s with his brand J.Lindeberg, has always believed in the power of blending style with sport. Teaming up with adidas, he seeks to once again redefine the golf apparel landscape by offering women golfers bold, dynamic designs that embrace both performance and fashion.</p><p><em>\u201cMy daughter Blue and I are excited to create this special collaboration with adidas,\u201d</em> Lindeberg says. <em>\u201cThis capsule speaks to the energy and inclusive community that\u2019s steadily growing in the sport, especially among women.\u201d</em></p><p>The collaboration draws on both Lindeberg\u2019s long-standing love for golf and his pioneering approach to design. With the rise of women in sports and the increasing desire for fashionable sportswear, the adidas x JAY3LLE capsule arrives at a crucial moment in the evolution of women\u2019s golf fashion.</p><h3><strong>Empowering Women on the Course</strong></h3><p>At the heart of the adidas x JAY3LLE capsule is the drive to empower women golfers to feel confident and stylish. The collection embraces modern sports apparel silhouettes through the lens of streetwear and high fashion, catering to a new generation of players who are challenging the traditional aesthetics of golf. It\u2019s a collection designed to inspire, energise, and push women to step out of their comfort zone on the course.</p><p><em>\u201cMore women are picking up the sport than ever before, and we want to be part of that driving force,\u201d</em> says Jennie Ko - adidas\u2019 global apparel design director.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
